    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="14"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2525</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your letter of May 24, with which
                    you transmitted a proposed letter of instructions to the Military Governor of
                    Santo Domingo.</p>
                <p>I concur entirely with the policy as outlined in your letter, as I feel it
                    advisable that steps should be taken at the earliest practicable date to relieve
                    the military forces of the United States from the performance of police duties
                    in the interior of the Dominican Republic. The plan outlined in the proposed
                    instruction should materially facilitate the eventual withdrawal of the Military
                    Government.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E. Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
